Indonesia Stocks: Bank Rakyat, Borneo Lumbung, Garuda Indonesia

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-07-29T09:20:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/indonesia-stocks-bank-rakyat-borneo-lumbung-garuda-indonesia.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  retreated 15.03 points, or 0.4
percent, to 4,130.80, falling for a second day. The measure
gained 6.2 percent this month, the most since September.  PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BBRI IJ), the nation’s second-
largest bank by assets, climbed 1.5 percent to 6,900 rupiah,
providing the biggest support to the Jakarta Finance Index. Bank
Rakyat’s first-half net income rose to 6.78 trillion rupiah
($797 million) from 4.32 trillion rupiah a year earlier, the
lender said in a statement published in  Bisnis Indonesia .  PT Borneo Lumbung Energi & Metal (BORN IJ), an Indonesian
coal producer, increased 2.2 percent to 1,400 rupiah, the
biggest gain since June 21. The company reported first-half net
income surged to 826.8 billion rupiah from 20.65 billion rupiah
a year earlier as revenue nearly tripled.  PT Cowell Development (COWL IJ), a property developer,
surged 35 percent to 178 rupiah, the steepest increase since
Dec. 19, 2007, after reporting first-half net income jumped 11-
fold from a year earlier to 29.83 billion rupiah.  PT Garuda  Indonesia  (GIAA IJ), Indonesia’s largest carrier,
dropped 1.9 percent to 510 rupiah. Garuda reported a 187.3
billion rupiah net loss in the first half, compared with profit
of 55.69 billion rupiah a year earlier, the company said.
Revenue in the six months ended June 30 rose to 11.21 trillion
rupiah from 7.76 trillion rupiah, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
